<p>Your programming toolbox, after one tutorial:</p>

<table class="cheat-Sheet">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>JavaScript</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code class="html"><%= '<script>' %></code></td><td>Where JavaScript lives &mdash; at the bottom of the <code class="html"><%= '<body>' %></code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>document.getElementById('name')</code></td><td>Finds the element with <code>id="name"</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>.textContent = ...</code></td><td>Changes the words inside an element</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>var name = ...</code></td><td>A named box: words, numbers, true/false, or lists</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>function name() { ... }</code></td><td>A named trick, performed with <code>name()</code></td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>onclick="name()"</code></td><td>Runs a function when something is clicked</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>if ( ... ) { } else { }</code></td><td>Choosing between two paths</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>&lt;</code> <code>&gt;</code> <code>&lt;=</code> <code>&gt;=</code> <code>==</code> <code>!=</code></td><td>Comparisons: questions that answer true or false</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>['a', 'b', 'c']</code> + <code>Math.random()</code></td><td>A list, and dice to pick from it</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>pets = pets + 1</code></td><td>Counting things that happen</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>new Date()</code></td><td>The visitor's current date and time</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

